        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>Yiddish</add>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <add>Yiddish</add>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><date>Tuesday, 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Tebet</date>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><date>(January) 1860</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">(<placeName>Savannah, Georgia</placeName>)</p>
            <p>Peace, etc. to <addressee>Rabbi Isaac</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Today I returned from a journey from<lb/>
                <placeName>Macon</placeName>, where I was yesterday. <persName>Mr.
                    Feucht-<lb/>wanger</persName> kept the holiday prayer-books and paid me.<lb/>
                You will find it enclosed. Recently, I sent you<lb/> a draft for $43.50, with regard
                to which you have<lb/> not replied to me. Please answer me this time whether<lb/>
                you received everything properly. When you have<lb/> the opportunity, send me a
                prayer book for $2.50<lb/> which has been ordered in <placeName>Macon</placeName> by
                someone named<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Hechster</persName>, and be good enough to send me some of<lb/> your
                books, called “More Darech”* in order to—<lb/> in <placeName>Israel</placeName>.
                Please send me the account. Aside from<lb/> this there is no news.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Your friend and servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Judah Hirschberg</persName>
            </p>
            <p>* a guide</p>
        </body>
    </text>
